1
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,100
♪I love the clarity in your eyes♪

2
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:13,860
♪Like a shooting star across my world♪

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,580
♪Repeating the goodbye we never said♪

4
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:21,540
♪Through sleepless nights♪

5
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,100
♪I miss the way you looked at me♪

6
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:30,260
♪Like photos freezing that summer bit by bit♪

7
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:35,380
♪By the shore with warm winds, maybe we'll meet again♪

8
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:41,460
[Fall in Love Again]

9
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:43,980
[Episode 9]

10
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,280
I said okay.

11
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:47,720
Really?

12
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:48,680
That's great.

13
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:49,640
Hold on. Wait.

14
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,640
Last night, I was your girlfriend.

15
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:53,040
But we're broken up now.

16
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:56,040
No.

17
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:57,080
I don't date kids.

18
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,480
I'm not a kid.

19
00:00:58,800 --> 00:00:59,640
[Delivery]
Alright.

20
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:01,120
You're not a kid.

21
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:02,320
Fine. You're not a kid.

22
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:02,960
Go.

23
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:04,000
You can leave now.

24
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:14,960
I'm an adult.

25
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:16,760
I'll take responsibility.

26
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,800
Take responsibility? How?

27
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:25,200
After we get married, are we living at my place

28
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,520
or your rented apartment?

29
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,640
I like men who've seen the world.

30
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,040
Not those still itching to explore it.

31
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:33,840
Last night

32
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:35,920
was just a one-night thing, no cameras involved.

33
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,160
Don't read into it.

34
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:38,440
And don't come looking for me again.

35
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,240
Please leave my place now.

36
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:42,300
♪Traces of a racing heart♪

37
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,940
♪Is it the sky or its reflection♪

38
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:49,420
♪I can't tell anymore♪

39
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:53,740
♪Lost in your eyes♪

40
00:01:56,260 --> 00:01:59,260
♪As we draw closer♪

41
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:02,420
♪The space of an embrace♪

42
00:02:03,020 --> 00:02:05,620
♪Scatters the dark♪

43
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:09,900
♪When the wind comes, raise the sails♪

44
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,180
♪And sail on...♪

45
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:16,040
Pretty good, actually.

46
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,840
Didn't I tell you already?

47
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,840
Don't come here again.

48
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,680
Why do you have to...

49
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,440
Who are you talking to?

50
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:30,920
You.

51
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,000
Who else?

52
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,000
Nothing. What's up?

53
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,320
I brought you breakfast.

54
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,720
Why'd you leave early last night?

55
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:37,520
Had too much to drink.

56
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,680
You already started eating?

57
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,280
Not yet.

58
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,760
Have a seat.

59
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:54,080
I knew we were in sync.

60
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,400
So I bought it for nothing?

61
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:57,920
Of course not.

62
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,040
What did you get?

63
00:02:59,120 --> 00:02:59,840
Wontons.

64
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:02,120
Wontons are my favorite.

65
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,320
Perfect. Let's eat together.

66
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,720
What's up? What happened?

67
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,040
I think we still have to push through

68
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,160
the company issues.

69
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,600
I feel the same.

70
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,400
I'll cover Mr. Wang's losses.

71
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,800
With what?

72
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,920
I've had finance sort it out.

73
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,600
All the assets I can liquidate,

74
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,960
stocks and funds.

75
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:23,560
Oh, right.

76
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,320
I'm selling my place and my car too.

77
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:27,800
We're thinking the same thing.

78
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,600
I've got some securities,

79
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,560
and bonds too.

80
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:33,080
But even combined, it doesn't seem enough.

81
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,600
What are you doing?

82
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,480
Didn't we agree I'd handle this?

83
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:38,280
Chu.

84
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,720
We signed the company contract together.

85
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,400
This is our company.

86
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,720
Can you stop taking all the blame

87
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,200
whenever something goes wrong?

88
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,560
Look at me.

89
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,120
Do I look like someone irresponsible?

90
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,240
No.

91
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:55,960
This whole thing...

92
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,640
When you noticed the contract issue,

93
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,880
it was me being stubborn,

94
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,200
and thinking I could handle it early on.

95
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,200
I didn't expect it to blow up like this.

96
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,600
I should be the one responsible.

97
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,760
You wanting to use Qi Siqin's share

98
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,920
to help the company. Was that wrong?

99
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,760
If we're both at fault,

100
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,760
then you were just overly confident.

101
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,920
And I failed to review it properly too.

102
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:16,480
Mr. Wang was introduced by me, right?

103
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,920
He's clearly setting us up now.

104
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,800
He's trying to screw us over.

105
00:04:18,830 --> 00:04:19,830
Even if not this time,

106
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:20,510
there'd be a next time,

107
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,640
and another after that.

108
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,200
It's Qi Siqin.

109
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,440
He's targeting me.

110
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,920
Didn't you say going against the current

111
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,440
was never going to be easy?

112
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:31,120
Chu.

113
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,600
Even without them, there'd be someone else.

114
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,680
The company can't hit trouble

115
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,200
and have us both blindly blame ourselves.

116
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,800
Origin was founded by the two of us.

117
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,520
So when it comes to the company,

118
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:46,080
we share honor and loss together.

119
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,480
We're in this together.

120
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,920
Alright.

121
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:52,040
Since President Yang is so bold,

122
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,240
then whatever money we can't make up,

123
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,120
I'll sell you to Mr. Wang to cover it.

124
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,240
You can't sell me. I'd be selling you.

125
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,440
The transfer clause is for agency rights.

126
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:04,720
Oh, right.

127
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:07,360
What about the actors already signed?

128
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:08,520
Don't worry.

129
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,760
I talked to all of them yesterday.

130
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,080
Right now, you're the one in the most danger.

131
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,040
Ms. Chu.

132
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:16,920
Time to sell everything we've got.

133
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,000
This place is a bit old,

134
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,040
but the location makes up for it.

135
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:30,480
You're selling in a rush,

136
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,000
and you want full cash upfront,

137
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,320
so the price won't go very high.

138
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,680
As long as it's no less than 80% of market value,

139
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,480
I can accept it.

140
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,800
But it has to be fast.

141
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,480
A lower price will move faster,

142
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,960
but you can't back out.

143
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:41,440
I won't.

144
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:41,920
Alright.

145
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,160
I'll contact buyers right away.

146
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:45,340
[Five Blessings Arrive]

147
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,200
This house was left to you by your grandpa.

148
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,280
You're really okay selling it?

149
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,480
He said it himself before.

150
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,240
The house is just an asset,

151
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,520
and it's meant for emergencies.

152
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:10,720
There's nothing

153
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,520
more urgent than this.

154
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:14,040
He meant it for your emergencies,

155
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:14,920
not

156
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,400
for someone else's, right?

157
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,200
She's not just anyone.

158
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:18,640
Let's go.

159
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:20,520
Hey, He.

160
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,240
Don't end up with nothing after all this.

161
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,120
I'm telling you...

162
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,520
I'm not doing this for anything in return.

163
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,920
What a hopeless romantic.

164
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:31,200
Come on, let's eat.

165
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,440
Mr. Wang.

166
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:42,520
Ms. Chu.

167
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,240
Li,

168
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,000
pour a cup of tea.

169
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,880
Ms. Chu is here.

170
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:47,840
No need for tea.

171
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,880
Mr. Wang, I'm here today to repay the money.

172
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,800
I know this amount isn't enough to cover the damages,

173
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:57,720
but I'm hoping

174
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,440
you can give me a few more days.

175
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,880
Ms. Chu, you're joking, right?

176
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:05,480
Wasn't the compensation already paid?

177
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,040
Paid?

178
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:07,840
Exactly.

179
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:08,800
Who paid it?

180
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,840
Your company did.

181
00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:14,580
[Yang]

182
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,200
Hello?

183
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,200
Chu.

184
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,120
Come back to the office now.

185
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,680
So, not bad, right? This company of mine.

186
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:30,840
Not bad.

187
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,440
You've really made something of yourself.

188
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:33,920
Of course.

189
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:37,840
Who's that?

190
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,240
You don't know him?

191
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:46,580
[Fortune Weekly]

192
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,240
What's the big deal?

193
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,440
If I hadn't sold my place to save the company,

194
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,320
would it have survived?

195
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:56,880
Bro.

196
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,440
You really think selling that place saved the company?

197
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:04,840
Xiwen.

198
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:06,800
Lucky I have you.

199
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,640
This time you returned

200
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,680
in glory.

201
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,880
Now I finally have someone backing me up.

202
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,600
Still, Mr. Wang took a huge advantage of us.

203
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,200
Feels like we really got the short end of it.

204
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,520
Business is a battlefield.

205
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,280
You have to learn to accept the outcome when you take a gamble.

206
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:26,200
Yeah, yeah, Professor Lecture.

207
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,640
Still love lecturing people.

208
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,040
So?

209
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,440
Wanna

210
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:34,000
I teach that Qi a lesson for you?

211
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,000
No need.

212
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,000
I don't want anything to do with him anymore.

213
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,600
Right now,

214
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:41,120
all I care about is making money.

215
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,840
That's the spirit.

216
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,600
Don't worry.

217
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,800
Now that I'm back,

218
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,840
no one will dare mess with you again.

219
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:52,480
From now on, I've got your back.

220
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,560
Listen to you...

221
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,040
That's really sweet.

222
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:04,240
Because in this world,

223
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,640
you're the only one I care about.

224
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,240
Don't move.

225
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,480
He's making a move.

226
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,520
If it were me, I'd go all in.

227
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,400
You idiot, you'd really rush in?

228
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,480
So you're Mr. Song?

229
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:23,860
[Clash of Psychic Beasts]

230
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,640
This is gonna get interesting.

231
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,720
And this is?

232
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,640
I'm also a partner of the company.

233
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,080
Thanks for coming all this way, Mr. Song.

234
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:50,920
Have some water.

235
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,200
Chu didn't neglect you, did she?

236
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,440
What did you just call me?

237
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,600
I forgot this is the office.

238
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,240
I should call you Ms. Chu.

239
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,560
This is our newly signed artist.

240
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,240
He Zheng.

241
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,920
He's young, don't take it personally.

242
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,800
Since when did you become my partner?

243
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,080
It's fine.

244
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,200
This young man's quite impressive.

245
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,320
Very promising.

246
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:27,520
Ms. Chu still has such a sharp eye.

247
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:28,800
Exactly.

248
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,640
Chu, she...

249
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:37,040
Ms. Chu really has good judgment.

250
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,800
Otherwise, how could she

251
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,200
pick me at first glance?

252
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:47,240
That's right, casting is crucial.

253
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,200
Otherwise the whole project would flop.

254
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,640
But Xi.

255
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:53,120
You shouldn't be too casual.

256
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,400
After all, this is the office.

257
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:58,880
And you're the boss.

258
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:02,280
People might get the wrong idea, don't you think?

259
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,200
He Zheng.

260
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:11,480
He Zheng.

261
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,960
Go talk to Yang about the IP.

262
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,080
The IP...

263
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,880
Just go.

264
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:23,640
Okay.

265
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,160
Xiwen.

266
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:29,800
Have some water.

267
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,920
Looks like the water here

268
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,600
isn't for just anyone.

269
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,080
Wow, they're not even trying to hide it.

270
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,720
He Zheng, tell me,

271
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,840
what exactly is going on between Mr. Song and Xi?

272
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:03,240
They grew up together. Childhood friends.

273
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,280
So what?

274
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:09,880
Hi, Yang.

275
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,520
What's up with your outfit?

276
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:14,640
I admit, today I...

277
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:15,400
Instead of working,

278
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,360
you're eavesdropping on your boss?

279
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,480
Besides,

280
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:21,760
you were standing so far away.

281
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:23,520
What could you possibly hear?

282
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,840
You've got a point, Yang.

283
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:37,720
Hey.

284
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,760
So you're really staying this time?

285
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:40,960
I'm not leaving.

286
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,680
What about the business overseas?

287
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:45,800
The domestic market is stronger than overseas right now.

288
